# 7. 美しい音

Toya: There! Right there.
Boy: Oh, it's starting to sound a lot better...!
Toya: Yes, you're right. Try doing that again for me.
Boy: O-Okay!
Boy: I get it now. I wasn't able to play the way I wanted because I was so focused on “playing properly”...
Mafuyu: That seems to be the case... But you should be able to play just fine now.
Kanade: You can do it...!
Boy: Thanks...!
Boy: *Inhale*
Boy: *Gasp*
An: Wait, that sounded really good just now!
Boy: Hehe...! L-Let me do that again...
Boy: I did it...! I can make sounds using just the mouthpiece now!
Toya: If you can produce this much sound, then you should be able to play the trumpet just fine after reattaching it.
Boy: Oh, you think so?
Toya: Yes, as long as you remember this sensation. Would you like to give it a try?
Boy: Y-Yeah...! Please let me try!
Toya: Okay. Then, we'll reattach your mouthpiece to the trumpet and...
Boy: ...
Toya: You should be able to play just fine now.
Toya: Try to stay relaxed. Believe in yourself...
Toya: Hold the love you have for the sound of the trumpet in your heart, and play.
Boy: O-Okay...!
Boy: Breathe in... Breathe out...
Boy: I'm going to succeed. I'm going to play...
Boy: *Gasp* D-Did you hear that...?!
Toya: Yes...! I heard it clearly!
Toya: That was a very beautiful sound.
Boy: I...! I did it...!
Boy: Thank you!
Boy: Thank you so much...!
An: Wow! You're playing like a pro now!
Mafuyu: Congratulations. That was beautiful.
Kanade: *Nod*
Kanade: I'm so glad you were able to play it.
Boy: Me too! And thank you two so much! I definitely wouldn't have been able to if you hadn't brought me over here!
Boy: I'm going to remember what happened today for the rest of my life!
Boy: I'm going to keep practicing... And perform in a concert someday!
Toya: That's wonderful.
Toya: I'll be looking forward to that day.
Marching Band Boys: Hey! We all have to meet back up now!
Boy: Oh! Hey, you guys! Guess what?! I can play the trumpet for real now!
Marching Band Boys: Wait, was that you playing just now?! That's awesome!
Boy: Hehe! I'm definitely going to play with you guys during our next concert!
Boy: Anyway, everyone! Thank you all very much!
Toya: You're welcome.
An: I wasn't sure what was gonna happen at first, but I'm so glad things ended up working out!
Toya: Me too.
Toya: I'm so glad that I was able to help him.
Kanade: Thank you both very much. You two really saved the day for us.
Kanade: Oh, also... I'm really sorry about just demoing the instruments without actually making any purchases.
Toya: No, that's okay. After all, this convention is about getting people interested in playing musical instruments. So, I really appreciate you for bringing him over.
Toya: Thank you for giving me this wonderful opportunity.
Toya: I felt genuine joy when he figured out how to play the trumpet the way he wanted.
Kanade: Huh?
Toya: The way his eyes glittered reminded me of...
Toya: How thrilled I was the first time I ever touched a piano.
Toya: And the first time I was able to play beautiful music using my own two hands.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: I also know that feeling.
Toya: You do?
Kanade: Yes.
Kanade: Because I also felt that incredible thrill when I played my dad's keyboard for the first time.
Kanade: I still remember that sound vividly.
Kanade: Each note seemed to sparkle and shine...
Kanade: I hope that boy looks back upon this day in a similar manner.
Toya: Yes, so do I.
Announcement: <We regret to inform all our attendees that Shibuya Instrument Day will be coming to a close momentarily.>
Announcement: <We thank you all very much for visiting. Please make sure not to forget any of your belongings.>
An: Whoa, look at the time! We gotta start packing up.
Mafuyu: Oh, that's right. You two need to keep working after this.
Mafuyu: Then, we'll excuse ourselves here. Thank you both again for helping us today.
Toya: No, it was our pleasure. I'm glad we got this chance to talk.
Toya: I hope we meet again soon.
Kanade: Us too.
An: Thanks for visiting! Get home safe, you two!
